page.title: 19Frankton Grounds,Fishpools.
page.content: Frankton Fishpools are to be found at the edge of Frankton village. They comprise of two pools,one large,one small.The large pool is used regularly by local fishermen.The main type of fishing is for carp and roach although other fish have also been caught there.The large pool is surrounded by water_reeds which are a haven for ducks and their families. There are many lily-pods to be seen floating on the pool and the whole area is full of interesting wildlife. The small pool, which is immediately next to the large pool,is unused by local fishermen.
